JCasC File-Based Secrets
========================

Each file in this directory becomes a resolvable ${FILENAME} variable in
casc.yaml. The filename must match exactly.

Required files:

  GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY   — SSH private key (PEM format) for the machine user
  GHCR_USERNAME            — GitHub username for container registry (ghcr.io)
  GHCR_TOKEN               — GitHub PAT with write:packages scope
  WEBHOOK_TOKEN            — Shared secret for GitHub webhook authentication

Setup:

  # SSH key (see README.md for machine user setup)
  cp ~/.ssh/my_deploy_key ./secrets/GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY
  chmod 600 ./secrets/GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY

  # GHCR credentials
  echo "your-github-username" > ./secrets/GHCR_USERNAME
  echo "ghp_your_personal_access_token" > ./secrets/GHCR_TOKEN

  # Webhook token (any random string)
  openssl rand -hex 20 > ./secrets/WEBHOOK_TOKEN

The SSH key should be a standard PEM-format SSH private key:

  -----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
  ...
  -----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----

IMPORTANT: Never commit secrets to git. The .gitignore excludes secrets/*
(except this README).
